    {
        "content": "<p>cfallin <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409#issuecomment-4490483692\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409\">issue #13409</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi: <code>cranelift-egraph</code> is no longer maintained -- we merged the egraph implementation back into our existing <code>cranelift-codegen</code> crate long ago. The old crate version still on <a href=\"http://crates.io\">crates.io</a> is an artifact of our project setup with multiple crates: when we delete a crate, we no longer publish new versions with new Cranelift/Wasmtime releases, so an old version remains forever on <a href=\"http://crates.io\">crates.io</a>.</p>\n<p>Maybe we should change that (e.g. publish a \"tombstone\" version that is empty, or yank the crate). @fitzgen @alexcrichton what do you think?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 596244258,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779212960
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409#issuecomment-4491271451\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409\">issue #13409</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Either seems fine by me. Also doing nothing is probably also fine, since this is the first spurious report we've had in many years of that crate not being active.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 596265467,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779218735
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409#issuecomment-4492405539\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13409\">issue #13409</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Personally I'd say we do nothing here, there's a fair number of <code>wasmtime-*</code> crates that are no longer maintained and I don't know the set that we'd have to go back and publish markers for.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 596295700,
